&lt;ul style=&quot;color: (33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;urban poverty rate&lt;/strong&gt; mentioned in the &lt;strong&gt;FY24 State Bank of India (SBI) Report&lt;/strong&gt; is 0.0409, which represents the proportion of the urban population living below the poverty line.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This data is derived from a detailed analysis by the &lt;strong&gt;Economic Research Department of the SBI&lt;/strong&gt;, which regularly publishes reports on various economic indicators in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poverty rate&lt;/strong&gt; is a critical measure of economic disparity, indicating the percentage of people unable to meet their basic needs for food, shelter, and other essentials.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The urban poverty rate in India has been declining over the years due to several factors, including &lt;strong&gt;government welfare schemes&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;job creation programs&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;urbanization&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
